Key BRs (IDs): BR 6	Employee separation can be triggered by resignation. A clearly identified offboarding approval workflow should be identified (e.g., Employee resigning > Line Manager > Financial approval > HR processing/approval).





Phase 3: Offboarding (OFF)

This phase manages the compliant separation of the employee, whether due to resignation or termination, focusing on asset recovery and final settlements.

Step	Requirement ID	User Story Summary / Action

1. Initiation (Employee)	OFF-018	Employee requests a Resignation request with reasoning.

2. Tracking Resignation	OFF-019	Employee tracks resignation request status.

3. Initiation (Manager/HR)	OFF-001	HR Manager initiates termination reviews based on warnings and performance data/manager requests.

4. Clearance Checklist	OFF-006	HR Manager uses an offboarding checklist for asset recovery (IT assets, ID cards, equipment).

5. Multi-Department Sign-off	OFF-010	HR Manager obtains multi-department exit clearance sign-offs (IT, Finance, Facilities, Line Manager).

6. System Revocation	OFF-007	System Admin revokes system and account access upon termination.

7. Final Settlement Trigger	OFF-013	HR Manager sends offboarding notification to trigger benefits termination and final pay calc



Phase III: Offboarding (Separation & Clearance)


13. Exit Initiation

Employee / HR Manager

Employee submits resignation [OFF-018] or HR initiates termination review [OFF-001].	US: OFF-018, OFF-019, OFF-001. BR: Separation may result from resignation or termination; justification mandatory.

Output: Resignation Request Submitted; Termination Review Started.

Data Flow: Status triggers workflow approval.




14. Clearance & Assets

HR Manager

Manage offboarding checklist and departmental sign-offs (IT, Finance, Facilities, etc.) [OFF-006, OFF-010].	US: OFF-006, OFF-010. BR: Multi-department clearance required; completion tracked.

Output: Offboarding Checklist Active; Clearance Sign-offs Logged.

Data Flow: Clearance governs final payroll release.


15. Security Revocation

	System Admin

Revoke system and account access on termination [OFF-007].	US: OFF-007. BR: Access revocation required for security.

Output: Access Disabled (Logged).

Data Flow: Logs stored in audit trail; confirms ONB-013 revocation.



16. Final Settlement

HR Manager

Trigger final pay calculation and benefits termination [OFF-013].	US: OFF-013. BR: Final pay includes unused leave, deductions, loans, severance; benefits auto-terminate.

Output: Final Pay Calculation Triggered; Benefits Termination Scheduled.


Data Flow: Sends encashment data from Leaves; triggers Payroll processing.







